{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-page-js","path":"/concepts/8-point-grid/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pivotal UI uses an 8-point grid system for sizing, spacing, and laying out components relative to one another. This means that any padding, margin, button height, etc. is always a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"multiple of 8 pixels"}]},{"type":"text","value":". This makes it easy to compose Pivotal UI components together neatly and consistently. For a deeper dive into how Pivotal arrived at the 8-point grid, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://builttoadapt.io/intro-to-the-8-point-grid-system-d2573cde8632"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"read this article"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/2000/1*Kcx60oAWZioon-V_RR-IQA.png","alt":"consistent spacing with a grid vs. inconsistent spacing without a grid"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using the 8-point grid"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pivotal UI incorporates the 8-point grid in several ways for different use cases."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Form, Panel & Table components"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Components like the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Form"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Panel"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Table"}]},{"type":"text","value":" have the 8-point grid built in, so using them means getting the benefits of the 8-point grid for free. For example, the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Form"}]},{"type":"text","value":" lays out all of its fields and labels according to the grid. For more information, see the individual component pages."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Grid & FlexCol components"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When more control is needed over layout, or when implementing custom components, the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Grid"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"FlexCol"}]},{"type":"text","value":" components can be used to lay out content according to the 8-point grid. For more information, see the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/components/grids"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Grids page"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Margin & padding modifiers"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The margin and padding CSS modifier classes (e.g. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"mtxl"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"